InfraSense
IR-Based Object Detection System

Designed using:
IR LED | Photodiode | LM358 Comparator

Created by:
Yaqub Baig Moghal

# Introduction

InfraSense is an IR-based object detection system designed from scratch by understanding the working principles of commercial IR sensor modules.

The system uses infrared reflection technology to detect nearby objects. It uses an IR transmitter, receiver, and LM358 comparator circuit to convert the received signal into a detection output.

# The main objectives of this project were:

• Understand the internal working of IR sensor modules
• Design a sensor circuit using basic electronic components
• Implement comparator-based signal detection
• Build and test a working hardware prototype
• Improve practical knowledge of analog electronics

| Component     | Purpose                     |
| ------------- | --------------------------- |
| IR LED        | Emits infrared light        |
| Photodiode    | Detects reflected IR signal |
| LM358 IC      | Works as voltage comparator |
| Potentiometer | Adjusts sensitivity         |
| Resistors     | Controls current flow       |
| LED           | Shows detection output      |
| Breadboard    | Circuit prototyping         |

# Working Principle.

The IR LED continuously transmits infrared rays.

When an object comes near the sensor, the rays reflect back and reach the photodiode.

The photodiode converts the received infrared signal into an electrical signal.

The LM358 comparator compares this signal voltage with the reference voltage set by the potentiometer.

Based on the comparison result, the output LED indicates object detection.

# Circuit Design Explenation. 

1. IR Transmitter Section

    The IR LED acts as a transmitter and generates infrared radiation continuously.

2. Receiver Section

    The photodiode detects reflected infrared light from nearby objects.

3. Comparator Section

    The LM358 compares input voltage levels and generates HIGH or LOW output based on detection conditions.

